The ANC president says the organisation will show its serious about the new dawn by dealing decisively with corruption. JOHANNESBURG - African National Congress (ANC) President Cyril Ramaphosa says the organisation will show its serious about the new dawn by dealing decisively with corruption. The president was speaking at a dialogue with professionals and academics In Sandton this evening. He says the organisation is on the path of renewal and rebuilding. ”We need to restore hope in the hearts and minds of our people about our seriousness in dealing with that which made their hope to plummet. One of those things is the whole problem and challenge of corruption. How we deal with corruption will define this new dawn.”